#. <section class="sutta" id="mn64"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn64:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 64"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 64"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn64:0.2"
msgid "Mahāmālukyasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse With Māluṅkya"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn64:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn64:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn64:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn64:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn64:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:2.1"
msgid ""
"“dhāretha no tumhe, bhikkhave, mayā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni "
"saṃyojanānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you remember the five lower fetters that I taught?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:2.2"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mālukyaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Māluṅkyaputta said to him:"

msgctxt "mn64:2.3"
msgid ""
"“ahaṃ kho, bhante, dhāremi bhagavatā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni "
"saṃyojanānī”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, I remember them.”"

msgctxt "mn64:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, dhāresi mayā desitāni "
"pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanānī”ti?"
msgstr "“But how do you remember them?”"

msgctxt "mn64:2.5"
msgid ""
"“Sakkāyadiṭṭhiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ "
"dhāremi;"
msgstr ""
"“I remember the lower fetters taught by the Buddha as follows: identity view,"

msgctxt "mn64:2.6"
msgid ""
"vicikicchaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ "
"dhāremi;"
msgstr "doubt,"

msgctxt "mn64:2.7"
msgid ""
"sīlabbataparāmāsaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ "
"desitaṃ dhāremi;"
msgstr "misapprehension of precepts and observances,"

msgctxt "mn64:2.8"
msgid ""
"kāmacchandaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ "
"dhāremi;"
msgstr "sensual desire,"

msgctxt "mn64:2.9"
msgid ""
"byāpādaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ desitaṃ dhāremi."
msgstr "and ill will."

msgctxt "mn64:2.10"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, dhāremi bhagavatā desitāni pañcorambhāgiyāni "
"saṃyojanānī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I remember the five lower fetters taught by the Buddha.”"

# Normally such constructions with nāma indicate reproval as at MN 22, etc. It is unclear why that tone is adopted here.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.433"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Kassa kho nāma tvaṃ, mālukyaputta, imāni evaṃ pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni "
"desitāni dhāresi?"
msgstr ""
"“Who on earth do you remember being taught the five lower fetters in that "
"way?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.2"
msgid ""
"Nanu, mālukyaputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā iminā taruṇūpamena upārambhena "
"upārambhissanti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t the wanderers who follow other paths fault you using the simile of "
"the infant?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.3"
msgid ""
"Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sakkāyotipi "
"na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sakkāyadiṭṭhi?"
msgstr ""
"For a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘identity’, so how could "
"identity view possibly arise in them?"

#. VAR: Anusetvevassa → anuseti tvevassa (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn64:3.4"
msgid "Anusetvevassa sakkāyadiṭṭhānusayo."
msgstr "Yet the underlying tendency to identity view still lies within them."

msgctxt "mn64:3.5"
msgid ""
"Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa dhammātipi "
"na hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati dhammesu vicikicchā?"
msgstr ""
"A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘teachings’, so how could doubt "
"about the teachings possibly arise in them?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.6"
msgid "Anusetvevassa vicikicchānusayo."
msgstr "Yet the underlying tendency to doubt still lies within them."

msgctxt "mn64:3.7"
msgid ""
"Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sīlātipi na "
"hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sīlesu sīlabbataparāmāso?"
msgstr ""
"For a little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘precepts’, so how could "
"misapprehension of precepts and observances possibly arise in them?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.8"
msgid "Anusetvevassa sīlabbataparāmāsānusayo."
msgstr ""
"Yet the underlying tendency to misapprehension of precepts and observances "
"still lies within them."

msgctxt "mn64:3.9"
msgid ""
"Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa kāmātipi na "
"hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati kāmesu kāmacchando?"
msgstr ""
"A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘sensual pleasures’, so how "
"could desire for sensual pleasures possibly arise in them?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.10"
msgid "Anusetvevassa kāmarāgānusayo."
msgstr "Yet the underlying tendency to sensual desire still lies within them."

msgctxt "mn64:3.11"
msgid ""
"Daharassa hi, mālukyaputta, kumārassa mandassa uttānaseyyakassa sattātipi na "
"hoti, kuto panassa uppajjissati sattesu byāpādo?"
msgstr ""
"A little baby doesn’t even have a concept of ‘sentient beings’, so how could "
"ill will for sentient beings possibly arise in them?"

msgctxt "mn64:3.12"
msgid "Anusetvevassa byāpādānusayo."
msgstr "Yet the underlying tendency to ill will still lies within them."

msgctxt "mn64:3.13"
msgid ""
"Nanu, mālukyaputta, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā iminā taruṇūpamena upārambhena "
"upārambhissantī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Wouldn’t the wanderers who follow other paths fault you using the simile of "
"the infant?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn64:4.2"
msgid "“etassa, bhagavā, kālo, etassa, sugata, kālo "
msgstr "“Now is the time, Blessed One! Now is the time, Holy One! "

msgctxt "mn64:4.3"
msgid ""
"yaṃ bhagavā pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni deseyya. Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū "
"dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"May the Buddha teach the five lower fetters. The mendicants will listen and "
"remember it.”"

msgctxt "mn64:4.4"
msgid "“Tena hānanda, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "mn64:4.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied."

msgctxt "mn64:4.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Idhānanda, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido "
"ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido "
"sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, take an uneducated ordinary person who has not seen the noble ones, "
"and is neither skilled nor trained in their teaching. They’ve not seen good "
"persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in their teaching. "

msgctxt "mn64:5.2"
msgid "sakkāyadiṭṭhipariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati sakkāyadiṭṭhiparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is overcome and mired in identity view,"

msgctxt "mn64:5.3"
msgid "uppannāya ca sakkāyadiṭṭhiyā nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they don’t truly understand the escape from identity view that has "
"arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:5.4"
msgid "Tassa sā sakkāyadiṭṭhi thāmagatā appaṭivinītā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"That identity view is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower "
"fetter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:5.5"
msgid "Vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati vicikicchāparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is overcome and mired in doubt,"

msgctxt "mn64:5.6"
msgid "uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr "and they don’t truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:5.7"
msgid "Tassa sā vicikicchā thāmagatā appaṭivinītā orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr "That doubt is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:5.8"
msgid ""
"Sīlabbataparāmāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati sīlabbataparāmāsaparetena;"
msgstr ""
"Their heart is overcome and mired in misapprehension of precepts and "
"observances,"

msgctxt "mn64:5.9"
msgid "uppannassa ca sīlabbataparāmāsassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they don’t truly understand the escape from misapprehension of precepts "
"and observances that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:5.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa so sīlabbataparāmāso thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"That misapprehension of precepts and observances is reinforced in them, not "
"eliminated: it is a lower fetter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.434"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:5.11"
msgid "Kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati kāmarāgaparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is overcome and mired in sensual desire,"

msgctxt "mn64:5.12"
msgid "uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they don’t truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has "
"arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:5.13"
msgid "Tassa so kāmarāgo thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"That sensual desire is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower "
"fetter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:5.14"
msgid "Byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati byāpādaparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is overcome and mired in ill will,"

msgctxt "mn64:5.15"
msgid "uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they don’t truly understand the escape from ill will that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:5.16"
msgid "Tassa so byāpādo thāmagato appaṭivinīto orambhāgiyaṃ saṃyojanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"That ill will is reinforced in them, not eliminated: it is a lower fetter."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.1"
msgid ""
"Sutavā ca kho, ānanda, ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido "
"ariyadhamme suvinīto, sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto na sakkāyadiṭṭhipariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na "
"sakkāyadiṭṭhiparetena;"
msgstr ""
"But an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is skilled and "
"trained in their teaching. They’ve seen good persons, and are skilled and "
"trained in their teaching. Their heart is not overcome and mired in identity "
"view,"

msgctxt "mn64:6.2"
msgid "uppannāya ca sakkāyadiṭṭhiyā nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they truly understand the escape from identity view that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:6.3"
msgid "Tassa sā sakkāyadiṭṭhi sānusayā pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"That identity view, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in "
"them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.4"
msgid "Na vicikicchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na vicikicchāparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is not overcome and mired in doubt,"

msgctxt "mn64:6.5"
msgid "uppannāya ca vicikicchāya nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "and they truly understand the escape from doubt that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:6.6"
msgid "Tassa sā vicikicchā sānusayā pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"That doubt, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.7"
msgid ""
"Na sīlabbataparāmāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na "
"sīlabbataparāmāsaparetena;"
msgstr ""
"Their heart is not overcome and mired in misapprehension of precepts and "
"observances,"

msgctxt "mn64:6.8"
msgid "uppannassa ca sīlabbataparāmāsassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they truly understand the escape from misapprehension of precepts and "
"observances that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:6.9"
msgid "Tassa so sīlabbataparāmāso sānusayo pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"That misapprehension of precepts and observances, along with any underlying "
"tendency to it, is given up in them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.10"
msgid "Na kāmarāgapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na kāmarāgaparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is not overcome and mired in sensual desire,"

msgctxt "mn64:6.11"
msgid "uppannassa ca kāmarāgassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"and they truly understand the escape from sensual desire that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:6.12"
msgid "Tassa so kāmarāgo sānusayo pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"That sensual desire, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up "
"in them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.13"
msgid "Na byāpādapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā viharati na byāpādaparetena;"
msgstr "Their heart is not overcome and mired in ill will,"

msgctxt "mn64:6.14"
msgid "uppannassa ca byāpādassa nissaraṇaṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr "and they truly understand the escape from ill will that has arisen."

msgctxt "mn64:6.15"
msgid "Tassa so byāpādo sānusayo pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"That ill will, along with any underlying tendency to it, is given up in them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:6.16"
msgid ""
"Yo, ānanda, maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya "
"taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ anāgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni ñassati vā "
"dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"There is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It’s "
"not possible to know or see or give up the five lower fetters without "
"relying on that path and that practice."

msgctxt "mn64:6.17"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato tacaṃ acchetvā "
"phegguṃ acchetvā sāracchedo bhavissatīti—"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a large tree standing with heartwood. It’s not possible to "
"cut out the heartwood without having cut through the bark and the softwood."

msgctxt "mn64:6.18"
msgid "netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn64:6.19"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, yo maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ anāgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni "
"saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower "
"fetters. It’s not possible to know or see or give up the five lower fetters "
"without relying on that path and that practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.435"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:7.1"
msgid ""
"Yo ca kho, ānanda, maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ āgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni "
"ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"There is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower fetters. It is "
"possible to know and see and give up the five lower fetters by relying on "
"that path and that practice."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:8.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato tacaṃ chetvā phegguṃ "
"chetvā sāracchedo bhavissatīti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a large tree standing with heartwood. It is possible to "
"cut out the heartwood after having cut through the bark and the softwood."

msgctxt "mn64:8.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, yo maggo yā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya taṃ maggaṃ taṃ paṭipadaṃ āgamma pañcorambhāgiyāni "
"saṃyojanāni ñassati vā dakkhati vā pajahissati vāti—ṭhānametaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there is a path and a practice for giving up the five lower "
"fetters. It is possible to know and see and give up the five lower fetters "
"by relying on that path and that practice."

msgctxt "mn64:8.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gaṅgā nadī pūrā udakassa samatittikā kākapeyyā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose the river Ganges was full to the brim so a crow could drink from it."

msgctxt "mn64:8.4"
msgid "Atha dubbalako puriso āgaccheyya:"
msgstr "Then along comes a feeble person, who thinks:"

#. VAR: gacchissāmī’ti → gacchāmīti (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn64:8.5"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ imissā gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ "
"gacchissāmī’ti;"
msgstr ""
"‘By swimming with my arms I’ll safely cross over to the far shore of the "
"Ganges.’"

msgctxt "mn64:8.6"
msgid ""
"so na sakkuṇeyya gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ "
"gantuṃ."
msgstr "But they’re not able to do so."

#. VAR: yesaṃ kesañci → yassa kassaci (sabbattha)
msgctxt "mn64:8.7"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, ānanda, yesaṃ kesañci sakkāyanirodhāya dhamme desiyamāne cittaṃ "
"na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the Dhamma is being taught for the cessation of "
"identity view, someone whose mind isn’t eager, confident, steady, and decided"

msgctxt "mn64:8.8"
msgid "seyyathāpi so dubbalako puriso evamete daṭṭhabbā."
msgstr "should be regarded as being like that feeble person."

msgctxt "mn64:8.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, gaṅgā nadī pūrā udakassa samatittikā kākapeyyā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose the river Ganges was full to the brim so a crow could drink from it."

msgctxt "mn64:8.10"
msgid "Atha balavā puriso āgaccheyya:"
msgstr "Then along comes a strong person, who thinks:"

msgctxt "mn64:8.11"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ imissā gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ "
"gacchissāmī’ti;"
msgstr ""
"‘By swimming with my arms I’ll safely cross over to the far shore of the "
"Ganges.’"

msgctxt "mn64:8.12"
msgid ""
"so sakkuṇeyya gaṅgāya nadiyā tiriyaṃ bāhāya sotaṃ chetvā sotthinā pāraṃ "
"gantuṃ."
msgstr "And they are able to do so."

msgctxt "mn64:8.13"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, ānanda, yesaṃ kesañci sakkāyanirodhāya dhamme desiyamāne cittaṃ "
"pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati;"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when the Dhamma is being taught for the cessation of "
"identity view, someone whose mind is eager, confident, steady, and decided"

msgctxt "mn64:8.14"
msgid "seyyathāpi so balavā puriso evamete daṭṭhabbā."
msgstr "should be regarded as being like that strong person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.436"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:9.1"
msgid ""
"Katamo cānanda, maggo, katamā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya?"
msgstr ""
"And what, Ānanda, is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower "
"fetters?"

msgctxt "mn64:9.2"
msgid ""
"Idhānanda, bhikkhu upadhivivekā akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānā sabbaso "
"kāyaduṭṭhullānaṃ paṭippassaddhiyā vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi "
"dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant—due to the seclusion from attachments, the giving up "
"of unskillful qualities, and the complete settling of physical discomfort—"
"quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, "
"enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss "
"born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "mn64:9.3"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ "
"viññāṇagataṃ te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato "
"ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati."
msgstr ""
"They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an "
"abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, "
"as empty, as not-self."

#. VAR: paṭivāpeti → paṭipāpeti (s1-3) | patiṭṭhāpeti (mr)
msgctxt "mn64:9.4"
msgid "So tehi dhammehi cittaṃ paṭivāpeti."
msgstr "They turn their mind away from those things,"

msgctxt "mn64:9.5"
msgid ""
"So tehi dhammehi cittaṃ paṭivāpetvā amatāya dhātuyā cittaṃ upasaṃharati:"
msgstr "and apply it to the deathless element:"

msgctxt "mn64:9.6"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, "
"the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, cessation, "
"extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "mn64:9.7"
msgid "So tattha ṭhito āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti;"
msgstr "Abiding in that they attain the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "mn64:9.8"
msgid ""
"no ce āsavānaṃ khayaṃ pāpuṇāti teneva dhammarāgena tāya dhammanandiyā "
"pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti, tattha "
"parinibbāyī, anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, with the ending of the five "
"lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously, because of their passion and "
"love for that meditation. They are extinguished there, and are not liable to "
"return from that world."

msgctxt "mn64:9.9"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya."
msgstr "This is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10-12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:10-12.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.4"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ "
"viññāṇagataṃ …"
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …"

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "They turn their mind away from those things …"

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.6"
msgid "anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously "
"… and are not liable to return from that world."

msgctxt "mn64:10-12.7"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya."
msgstr ""
"This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:13.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā "
"paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond perceptions of form, with the "
"ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions of "
"diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "mn64:13.2"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …"
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …"

msgctxt "mn64:13.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "They turn their mind away from those things …"

msgctxt "mn64:13.4"
msgid "anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously "
"… and are not liable to return from that world."

msgctxt "mn64:13.5"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya."
msgstr ""
"This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:14.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"space, aware that ‘consciousness is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "mn64:14.2"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …"
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …"

msgctxt "mn64:14.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "They turn their mind away from those things …"

msgctxt "mn64:14.4"
msgid "anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously "
"… and are not liable to return from that world."

msgctxt "mn64:14.5"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāya."
msgstr ""
"This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli1.437"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:15.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, ānanda, bhikkhu sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi "
"kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant, going totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness, aware that ‘there is nothing at all’, enters and remains in "
"the dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "mn64:15.2"
msgid ""
"So yadeva tattha hoti vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ …"
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there as impermanent …"

msgctxt "mn64:15.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "They turn their mind away from those things …"

msgctxt "mn64:15.4"
msgid "anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"If they don’t attain the ending of defilements, they’re reborn spontaneously "
"… and are not liable to return from that world."

msgctxt "mn64:15.5"
msgid ""
"Ayampi kho, ānanda, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ pahānāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"This too is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower fetters.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:16.1"
msgid ""
"“Eso ce, bhante, maggo esā paṭipadā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"pahānāya, atha kiñcarahi idhekacce bhikkhū cetovimuttino ekacce bhikkhū "
"paññāvimuttino”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, if this is the path and the practice for giving up the five lower "
"fetters, how come some mendicants here are released in heart while others "
"are released by wisdom?”"

# Reading tesaham
#. VAR: Ettha kho panesāhaṃ → ettha kho tesāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn64:16.2"
msgid "“Ettha kho panesāhaṃ, ānanda, indriyavemattataṃ vadāmī”ti."
msgstr "“In that case, I say it is the diversity of their faculties.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn64:16.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn64:16.4"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti."
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn64:16.5"
msgid "Mahāmālukyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
